From: Denis Nash <den7@cdc.gov>
Factors Affecting the Case Fatality Ratio
-----------------------------------------
In addition to the inoculum, other factors affecting the case fatality
ratio could be a higher denominator (i.e., better case finding and/or
inclusion of a broader spectrum of illness in the case definition) or
increases in the sensitivity of the laboratory test.
Does anyone dare consider that the estimates of the case fatality rate from
the Zaire experience were possibly inflated or overestimated? An important
question in this debate is how the denominators were defined and obtained
in each of the case fatality ratio assessments.
--
Denis Nash, PhD, MPH
Medical Epidemiologist
NYC Dept. of Health
Office of HIV/AIDS Surveillance
New York, NY
<den7@cdc.gov>

